		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Capital budgeting</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<p><b>Capital budgeting</b> (or investment appraisal) is the planning process used to determine whether a firm's long term <a href="/wiki/Investment" title="Investment">investments</a> such as new machinery, replacement machinery, new plants, new products, and research development projects are worth pursuing. It is budget for major capital, or investment, expenditures.<sup id="cite_ref-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-0" title=""><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<p>Many formal methods are used in capital budgeting, including the techniques such as</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="/wiki/Net_present_value" title="Net present value">Net present value</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Profitability_index" title="Profitability index">Profitability index</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Internal_rate_of_return" title="Internal rate of return">Internal rate of return</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Modified_Internal_Rate_of_Return" title="Modified Internal Rate of Return">Modified Internal Rate of Return</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Equivalent_Annual_Cost" title="Equivalent Annual Cost" class="mw-redirect">Equivalent annuity</a></li>
</ul>
<p>These methods use the incremental cash flows from each potential investment, or <i>project</i>. Techniques based on accounting earnings and accounting rules are sometimes used - though economists consider this to be improper - such as the <i>accounting rate of return,</i> and "<a href="/wiki/Return_on_investment" title="Return on investment" class="mw-redirect">return on investment</a>." Simplified and hybrid methods are used as well, such as <i><a href="/wiki/Payback_period" title="Payback period">payback period</a></i> and <i>discounted payback period</i>.</p>
<table id="toc" class="toc" summary="Contents">
<tr>
